The paper presents a method that combines machine learning with simple NR metrics to achieve a quality index comparable to FR algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with video quality assessment. Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms indicates that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the consideration of lossy network conditions suggests that the paper could also belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
